# Per-topic raw/ — large/binary user uploads stay local by default.
# Markdown sidecars (.meta.md) and any text/markdown extract are still tracked,
# so provenance lives in git even when the binary itself does not.
# To intentionally share a binary, run: git add -f path/to/file.pdf
# See raw/README.md → "File-size & copyright defaults" for rationale.
topics/*/raw/user/*.pdf
topics/*/raw/user/*.epub
topics/*/raw/user/*.mobi
topics/*/raw/user/*.mp4
topics/*/raw/user/*.mov
topics/*/raw/user/*.mkv
topics/*/raw/user/*.mp3
topics/*/raw/user/*.wav
topics/*/raw/user/*.flac
topics/*/raw/user/*.zip
topics/*/raw/user/*.tar
topics/*/raw/user/*.tar.gz
topics/*/raw/user/*.tgz
topics/*/raw/user/*.7z
topics/*/raw/user/*.rar
topics/*/raw/user/*.docx
topics/*/raw/user/*.pptx
topics/*/raw/user/*.xlsx
